on%20under%20control.%20Inflation%20has%20since%20slowed%20significantly%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20bit%20above%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20but%20they%20often%20trend%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20policy%20moves.%20This%20is%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20change%20based%20on%20investor%20demand%20for%20mortgage-backed%20securities%2C%20and%20this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20policy%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20lowered%20rates%20three%20times%20in%202024%2C%20but%20it%20may%20not%20cut%20as%20much%20in%202025.%20This%20means%20mortgage%20rates%20may%20only%20ease%20a%20little%20bit%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d9a91a2-bbb7-4944-a35e-77d4be3886d4%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Low%20Will%20Rates%20Go%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Low%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20there's%20still%20some%20uncertainty%20around%20how%20the%20economy%20will%20evolve%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20and%20years%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20say%20exactly%20where%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20end%20up.%20But%20they%20may%20not%20drop%20as%20much%20as%20initially%20anticipated%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20rates%20end%20up%20falling%20substantially%2C%20they're%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year%20fixed%20rates%20fell%20below%203%25.%20Rates%20are%20expected%20to%20continue%20to%20ease%20throughout%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two%2C%20and%20we%20may%20ultimately%20see%20rates%20settle%20in%20somewhere%20in%20the%206%25%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b20e8ddb-846d-4994-8400-746d066622e3%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Work%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Do%20Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20mortgage%20interest%20rate%20is%20how%20much%20you'll%20pay%20to%20borrow%20money%20for%20a%20home%20purchase%20or%20refinance.%20Each%20month%2C%20you'll%20make%20a%20payment%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20funds%20you%20borrowed%2C%20and%20a%20portion%20of%20that%20payment%20will%20go%20toward%20paying%20the%20interest%20you%20owe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20portion%20of%20your%20monthly%20payment%20that%20goes%20toward%20interest%20will%20go%20down%20over%20time%20through%20a%20process%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fmortgage-amortization-schedule%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eamortization%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20you%20pay%20off%20more%20of%20your%20mortgage%2C%20the%20loan%20balance%20is%20reduced%2C%20lowering%20your%20interest%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20say%20you%20get%20a%20mortgage%20of%20%24300%2C000%20with%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%206.5%25%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%20Every%20month%2C%20you'll%20pay%20about%20%241%2C896.%20On%20your%20very%20first%20mortgage%20payment%2C%20only%20%24271%20of%20that%20amount%20will%20go%20toward%20reducing%20your%20loan%20balance%2C%20while%20%241%2C625%20will%20be%20paid%20in%20interest.%20But%20if%20you%20fast%20forward%2020%20years%2C%20%24992%20of%20that%20same%20monthly%20payment%20will%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20loan%20balance%2C%20and%20about%20%24905%20will%20go%20toward%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20ask%20your%20lender%20for%20an%20amortization%20schedule%20to%20see%20the%20breakdown%20of%20your%20payments%20throughout%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20or%20you%20can%20use%20an%20online%20amortization%20calculator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212fb34fd-4a31-48cc-8f22-f83ef7f5937e%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Often%20Do%20Rates%20Change%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Often%20Do%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Change%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20change%20throughout%20the%20day%2C%20and%20they%20can%20fluctuate%20day-to-day%20or%20week-to-week%20based%20on%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20the%20economy.%20If%20economic%20conditions%20are%20relatively%20stable%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20might%20not%20move%20much.%20But%20uncertainty%20or%20expectations%20that%20conditions%20will%20change%20soon%20can%20send%20rates%20up%20or%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22619d777a-f117-47ba-8d95-4b58d07f112c%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20Shop%20for%20Rates%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20Shop%20for%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMortgage%20lenders%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20all%20offer%20the%20exact%20same%20rates%2C%20so%20you%20could%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20by%20shopping%20around%20for%20the%20best%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20generally%20recommend%20getting%20quotes%20from%20a%20few%20different%20lenders%20%E2%80%94%20consider%20applying%20with%20at%20least%20three%20lenders%20to%20get%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20range%20of%20rates%20available%20to%20you.%20If%20you're%20still%20early%20in%20the%20process%2C%20you%20can%20apply%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fmortgage-preapproval%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreapproval%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20get%20an%20estimate%20of%20your%20rate%20while%20you're%20still%20searching%20for%20homes.%20If%20you're%20under%20contract%20on%20a%20home%2C%20you%20can%20apply%20for%20regular%20approval%2C%20which%20will%20give%20you%20a%20more%20accurate%20picture%20of%20what%20you'll%20pay%20with%20a%20given%20lender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20sure%20to%20look%20at%20the%20overall%20offer.%20If%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20lot%20in%20fees%20to%20get%20a%20lower%20rate%2C%20it%20might%20not%20be%20worth%20it.%20Also%20consider%20other%20benefits%20and%20features%20that%20are%20important%20to%20you%2C%20like%20if%20a%20lender%2