20have%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20arrival%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-had-three-daughters-so-theyd-look-after-each-other-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird%20daughter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20discovered%20an%20assemblage%20of%20unexpected%20surprises%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20which%20caught%20me%20off%20guard%2C%20even%20as%20an%20experienced%20parent.%20At%20first%20it%20was%20more%20noise%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-house-messy-because-i-let-my-kids-be-kids-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emessier%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20washing%20machine%20literally%20never%20rests%20and%20the%20floors%20are%20always%20covered%20in%20crumbs.%20But%20then%2C%20there%20was%20more.%20Here%20are%20seven%20ways%20having%20a%20third%20child%20changed%20our%20lives%20in%20ways%20we%20didn't%20expect%20%E2%80%94%20some%20good%2C%20some%20a%20little%20tricky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e4f9a5b-751d-4be5-a369-e7930145b6b8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EExperience%20means%20nothing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20already%20have%20children%2C%20nothing%20will%20prepare%20you%20for%20the%20new%20newborn%20phase%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fage-gap-between-my-kids-makes-them-both-only-children-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive-year%20hiatus%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20remember%20thinking%20the%20first%20few%20months%20would%20be%20like%20riding%20a%20bike%3B%20I%20would%20hop%20on%20the%20momcycle%20and%20take%20off%20without%20any%20wobbling.%20However%2C%20the%20way%20a%20newborn%20cries%2C%20eats%2C%20sleeps%2C%20poops%2C%20blinks%20will%20never%20be%20the%20same%20as%20your%20previous%20babies.%20Parents%20have%20to%20learn%20a%20whole%20new%20language%20of%20baby%20communication%20with%20each%20child.%20And%20it%20doesn't%20get%20easier%3B%20while%20newborns%20are