permits%20for%20an%20additional%2018%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20strategic%20effort%20to%20safeguard%20the%20rights%20of%20vulnerable%20immigrants%2C%20who%20have%20been%20living%20and%20working%20in%20the%20US%20under%20TPS.%20By%20extending%20the%20program%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20effectively%20putting%20in%20place%20a%20temporary%20barrier%20against%20any%20potential%20attempts%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20dismantle%20or%20significantly%20alter%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETPS%20has%20become%20a%20contentious%20issue%2C%20with%20Republicans%20arguing%20that%20it%20has%20been%20granted%20too%20liberally%20to%20too%20many%20foreigners%2C%20and%20acts%20as%20a%20draw%20to%20migrants%20to%20come%20to%20the%20US%20illegally.%20However%2C%20the%20program%20has%20been%20expanded%20aggressively%20under%20Biden%2C%20with%20over%201%20million%20people%20from%2017%20countries%20currently%20living%20in%20the%20US%20under%20TPS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20extension%20of%20TPS%20for%20Venezuelans%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20significant%2C%20given%20the%20country's%20ongoing%20humanitarian%20crisis.%20The%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20(DHS)%20cited%20the%20%26quot%3Binhumane%26quot%3B%20government%20of%20Venezuelan%20President%20Nicol%C3%A1s%20Maduro%2C%20who%20was%20sworn%20in%20for%20a%20third%20term%20on%20Friday%2C%20as%20justification%20for%20the%20extension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECountries%20affected%20by%20the%20TPS%20extension%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Venezuela%3A%20Over%20600%2C000%20Venezuelans%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20extension%2C%20which%20is%20based%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bhumanitarian%20emergency%26quot%3B%20the%20country%20continues%20to%20face%20due%20to%20political%20and%20economic%20crises%20under%20the%20Maduro%20regime.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20El%20Salvador%3A%20More%20than%20230%2C000%20Salvadorans%20are%20protected%20under%20the%20program%2C%20which%20was%20first%20extended%20to%20the%20country%20in%202001%20after%20a%20series%20of%20earthquakes.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Ukraine%3A%20Approximately%20100%2C000%20people%20from%20Ukraine%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20extension%2C%20which%20is%20based%20on%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20the%20region.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-%20Sudan%3A%201%2C900%20individuals%20from%20Sudan%20will%20also%20benefit%20from%20the%20extension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TPS%20program%20was%20established%20under%20President%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Immigration%20Act%20of%201990.%20It%20is%20intended%20to%20provide%20foreigners%20already%20in%20the%20US%20with%20protections%20from%20deportation%20amid%20political%20strife%2C%20natural%20disasters%2C%20or%20armed%20conflict%20in%20their%20home%20countries.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736592840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Ft8ja6hp8_joe-biden-afp_625x300_11_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-joe-biden-saves-about-a-million-immigrants-from-deportation-before-leaving-7450104%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20move%20that%20could%20potentially%20delay%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20plans%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20immigration%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20extended%20Temporary%20Protected%20Status%20(TPS)%20for%20over%20900%2C000%20immigrants.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20flight%20attendants%20make%20at%20American%2C%20Delta%2C%20and%20United.%20Some%20can%20earn%20over%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225978%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Delta%20Airlines%20flight%20attendant%20waves%20from%20atop%20the%20boarding%20stairs.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67800e498951662c9f1f726