t%3B%20schedule.%20%26quot%3BReserve%26quot%3B%20crew%2C%20or%20those%20on%20call%2C%20have%20a%20minimum%20of%2075%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20translates%20to%20at%20least%20%2430%2C500%20for%20first-year%20crew%20and%20%2470%2C000%20for%20thirteen-year%20veterans%20before%20taxes%20and%20other%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20new%20contract%2C%20pay%20will%20increase%20in%20October%202025%20and%20again%20each%20year%20through%202029.%20By%20then%2C%20hourly%20rates%20will%20increase%20to%20a%20starting%20base%20pay%20of%20about%20%2440%20per%20hour%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20added%20boarding%20pay%20to%20its%20latest%20contract%20at%2050%25%20of%20a%20flight%20attendant's%20hourly%20rate%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20in%20March.%20This%20will%20further%20up%20the%20cabin%20crew's%20annual%20salary.%20Historically%2C%20crew%20were%20not%20paid%20for%20boarding%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20has%20historically%20not%20paid%20a%20high%20profit-sharing%20bonus.%20In%202023%2C%20it%20was%20just%201.1%25.%20The%20new%20contract%20increased%20that%20profit-sharing%20formula%20to%20match%20Delta's%2C%20but%20the%20final%20amount%20will%20depend%20on%20American's%20year-end%20earnings.%20For%202023%2C%20the%20airline%20was%20the%20least%20profitable%20of%20the%20Big%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ff06146-5025-46d8-ba68-4ffa461f7fe3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelta%20Air%20Lines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFirst-year%3A%20%2435.50%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E13th-year%3A%20%2479.80%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-flight-attendant-applications-overloaded-website-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDelta's%20flight%20attendants%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20not%20unionized.%20Their%20most%20recent%20pay%20bump%20was%20in%20June%2C%20which%20increased%20cabin%20crew%20salaries%20by%20about%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst-year%20Delta%20flight%20attendants%20earn%20a%20base%20pay%20of%20%2435.50%20an%20hour%2C%20while%2013-year%20crew%20members%20earn%20about%20%2480%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20American%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-flight-attendant-getting-paid-boarding-process-worst-part-job-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Delta%20cabin%20crew%20get%20boarding%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E%20equal%20to%20half%20of%20their%20hourly%20rate.%20In%202022%2C%20Delta%20became%20the%20first%20major%20US%20airline%20to%20offer%20the%20extra%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlight%20attendant%20salaries%20at%20Delta%20vary%20based%20on%20hours%20worked%20a%20month%20and%20there%20is%20no%20contractual%20minimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Delta%20flight%20attendants%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20unionize%20say%20the%20lack%20of%20guaranteed%20hours%20could%20lead%20to%20lower%20pay%20than%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Delta%20spokesperson%20said%20flight%20attendants%20typically%20get%2080%20hours%20a%20month.%20This%20means%20first-year%20and%2013-year%20flight%20attendants%20earn%20about%20%2434%2C000%20and%20%2476%2C600%20annually%2C%20before%20taxes%20and%20other%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20cabin%20crew%20can%20earn%20up%20to%20%241%2C200%20extra%20annually%20for%20meeting%20monthly%20operating%20metrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDelta%20also%20consistently%20distributes%20the%20highest%20annual%20profit-sharing.%20It%20paid%20%241.4%20billion%20to%20employees%20in%202023%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20a%20bonus%20of%2010.4%25%20of%20employees'%20eligible%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c424c45-3f4d-43d9-aec4-db8bfb05d6f2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnited%20Airlines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFirst-year%3A%20%2428.88%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E13th-year%3A%20%2467.11%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUnited%20has%20the%20lowest%20first-year%20base%20pay%20at%20about%20%2429%20an%20hour.%20Thirteen-year%20flight%20attendants%20make%20about%20%2467%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnited%20guarantees%2071%20hours%20of%20pay%20a%20month%20for%20those%20with%20a%20line%20schedule%2C%20while%20a%20reserve%20crew%20member%20gets%20a%20minimum%20of%2078%20hours.%20United%20does%20not%20currently%20offer%20boarding%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20amounts%20to%20United%20first-years%20making%20at%20least%20%2424%2C600%20a%20year%20and%2013-year%20flight%20attendants%20making%20at%20least%20%2457%2C000%20annually%20before%20taxes%20and%20other%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFailed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-flight-attendants-picketed-airports-pay-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiations%20between%20United%20and%20its%20labor%20union%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Association%20of%20Flight%20Attendants-CWA%2C%20have%20prevented%20pay%20increases%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20airline's%20wages%20are%20comparatively%20lower.%20Mediation%20of%20a%20new%20contract%20has%20been%20paused%20until%20at%20least%20early%20this%20year%2C%20so%20United%20cabin%20crew%20are%20still%20being%20paid%202021%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20United%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20half%20of%20the%20airline's%20cabin%20crew%20are%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20seniority%20pay%20scale%2C%20with%20average%20annual%20pay%20in%20that%20group%20hitting%20nearly%20%2480%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20likely%20accounts%20for%20hours%20worked%20above%20the%20guarantee%2C%20as%20United%20said%20the%20crews%20have%20flexible%20schedules%20and%20can%20work%20when%20they%20want%2C%20or%20other%20ways%20to%20earn%20extra%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnited%20said%20it%20has%20proposed%20a%2022.5%25%20raise%20and%20new%20boarding%20pay%2C%20among%20other%20offerings%2C%20as%20part%20of%20its%20contract%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union%20told%20BI%20it%20wants%20industry-leading%20pay%20and%20better%20work%20rules%20and%20scheduling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20lower%20comparative%20base%20pay%2C%20United%20flight%20attendants%20have%20earned%20high%20profit-sharing%20bonuses.%20In%202023%2C%20that%20was%20about%209.2%25%20of%20their%20eligible%20annual%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ab716f58-2f9c-4f91-8616-a2888bc3f207%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20ways%20flight%20attendants%20earn%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExtra%20pay%20opportunities%20can%20add%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20flight%20attendants'%20base%20rates%20and%20put%20the%20most%20senior%20crew%20members%20well%20into%20the%20six%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20working%20overtime%2C%20flying%20on%20holidays%20or%20during%20nighttime%2C%20or%20if%20they%20hold%20a%20skilled%20position.%20Airlines%20also%20offer%20flight%20attendants%20free%20flights%20for%20personal%20use%20as%20part%20of%20their%20employment%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkilled%20positions%20can%20include%20being%20the%20in-charge%20%26quot%3Blead%26quot%3B%20or%20purser%2C%20working%20in%20the%20galley%2C%20or%20speaking%20a%20second%20language.%20The%20premium%20pay%20ranges%20from%20%241%20to%20%247.50%20extra%20per%20hour%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20aircraft%20and%20whether%20the%20flight%20is%20domestic%20or%20international.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlight%20attendants%20also%20get%20per%20diem%20pay%2C%20typically%20%242%20to%20%244%20for%20each%20hour%20on%20duty%20away%20from%20home%2C%20to%20cover%20work-related%20expenses%20like%20meals%2C%20laundry%2C%20and%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20flight%20attendants%20can%20gross%20%24100%2C000%20or%20more%20annually%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20many%20hours%20they%20work.%20Premium%20and%20special%20skills%20pay%20help%20boost%20that.%20They%20can%20fly%20more%20hours%20by%20bidding%20for%20more%20than%20their%20monthly%20minimum%20or%20picking%20up%20trips%20dropped%20by%20other%20crew%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-salary-average-delta-american-united-2025-