term%20care%20%E2%80%94%20including%20assisted%20living%20and%20home%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20is%20largely%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20the%20broad%20middle%20class.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20growing%20population%20of%20older%20Americans%20is%20facing%20unaffordable%20long-term%20care.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20costs%20will%20also%20burden%20many%20younger%20people%20caring%20for%20older%20relatives%20and%20kin.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGovernment%20incentives%20and%20public%20insurance%20could%20help%20address%20care%20affordability%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20population%20of%20older%20Americans%20balloons%2C%20the%20financial%20costs%20associated%20with%20aging%20are%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20millennials%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-retirement-savings-crisis-401k-kids-parents-work-caregiving-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Xers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20facing%20a%20stark%20reality%3A%20their%20parents%20and%20grandparents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-homeowners-at-risk-of-homelessness-retirement-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20have%20the%20means%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20pay%20for%20long-term%20care%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they'll%20need%20to%20help%20foot%20the%20bill%2C%20especially%20since%20government%20aid%20often%20doesn't%20cover%20large%20parts%20of%20this%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20younger%20people%20end%20up%20leaving%20their%20jobs%20or%20working%20less%20in%20order%20to%20care%20for%20their%20aging%20family%20members%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20sacrifice%20can%20hurt%20them%20financially%20both%20today%20and%20in%20the%20future%2C%20including%20by%20shrinking%20their%20income%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-medicaid-snap-benefits-income-reliance-increases-aging-population-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bigger%20issue%20is%20you%20can%20create%20almost%20a%20cycle%20of%20poverty%2C%26quot%3B%20Marc%20Cohen%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20gerontology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Massachusetts%20Boston%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20something%20that%20just%20sticks%20with%20one%20generation.%20The%20costs%20are%20borne%20communally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224e759c04-9af2-427c-bf1d-89a689f44958%5C%22%3EUnprepared%20for%20a%20predictable%20crisis%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20other%20forms%20of%20care%20%E2%80%94%20from%20emergency%20rooms%20to%20daycares%20%E2%80%94%20the%20labor%20and%20facilities%20needed%20for%20long-term%20care%20don't%20come%20cheap.%20A%20shortage%20of%20long-term%20care%20workers%2C%20coupled%20with%20inflation%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F14%2Fhealth%2Flong-term-care-facilities-costs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esent%20prices%20up%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20the%20oldest%20members%20of%20the%20baby%20boomer%20generation%20near%2080%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20these%20services%20is%20expected%20to%20rise%20sharply%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0putting%20upward%20pressure%20on%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivately-provided%20long-term%20care%20%E2%80%94%20including%20assisted%20living%20communities%20and%20home%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20is%20largely%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20the%20broad%20middle%20class.%20Fewer%20than%2015%25%20of%20people%2075%20and%20over%20living%20alone%20in%20major%20US%20cities%20could%20afford%20to%20pay%20for%20assisted%20living%20or%20daily%20home%20health%20aide%20visits%20without%20dipping%20into%20their%20assets%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fhousing-americas-older-adults-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202023%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Harvard%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20affordability%20issue%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20middle%20market%2C%20that%20concerns%20us%20the%20most%2C%26quot%3B%20Lisa%20McCracken%2C%20head%20of%20research%20and%20analytics%20at%20the%20National%20Investment%20Center%20for%20Seniors%20Housing%20%26amp%3B%20Care%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetirees%20and%20their%20families%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20rely%20on%20the%20government%20to%20help.%20Medicare%2C%20the%20government's%20health%20insurance%20program%20for%20older%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncoa.org%2Farticle%2Fdoes-medicare-pay-for-assisted-living%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoesn't%20cover%20most%20long-term%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20assisted%20living%2C%20home%20healthcare%2C%20and%20nursing%20homes.%20Medicaid%20largely%20doesn't%20cover%20assisted%20living%20and%20home%20healthcare%2C%20and%20there%20are%20often%20long%20waitlists%20for%20the%20nursing%20home%20care%20it%20does%20cover.%20Some%20assisted%20living%20residents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F04%2F06%2Fseniors-assisted-living-medicaid-eviction%2F%3Futm_source%3Dtwitter%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_campaign%3Dwp_main%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20evicted%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20they%20spent%20down%20their%20savings%20and%20were%20forced%20to%20rely%20on%20Medicaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20thought%2C%20'Oh%2C%20well%2C%20doesn't%20Medicare%20pay%20for%20this%3F'%20and%20it%20does%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20people%20find%20out%20late%20in%20life%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20any%20protection%20against%20these%20costs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20happened%20to%20Erika%20Gilles%20and%20her%20family.%20After%20Gilles'%2078-year-old%20mother%2C%20Karen%20Proctor%2C%20was%20hospitalized%20for%20her%20chronic%20kidney%20disease%20last%20year%2C%20she%20quickly%20realized%20her%20mother's%20Medicare%20coverage%20wouldn't%20be%20enough%20to%20cover%20her%20long-term%20care.%20Overnight%2C%20her%20mother%20went%20from%20living%20independently%20in%20the%20house%20she's%20long%20owned%20to%20requiring%20dialysis%20treatment%20and%20constant%20care.%20But%20Gilles%20couldn't%20purchase%20private%20long-term%20care%20insurance%20because%20of%20her%20mother's%20pre-existing%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGilles%2C%2057%2C%20found%20a%20group%20assisted%20living%20facility%20for%20her%20mother%2C%20who%20applied%20for%20a%20state%20subsidy%20to%20help%20cover%20the%20cost.%20If%20the%20subsidy%20doesn't%20come%20through%2C%20Gilles%20is%20worried%20they'll%20have%20to%20sell%20her%20mother's%20house%20in%20Sun%20City%2C%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20totally%20turned%20my%20life%20upside%20down.%20It's%20absorbed%20all%20of%20my%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Gilles%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I'm%20ever%20going%20to%20retire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22878f7983-1ed6-4131-b7af-8d67e70e0b73%5C%22%3EIt's%20not%20just%20a%20boomer%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-retirement-savings-crisis-401k-kids-parents-work-caregiving-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20sandwiched%20between%20caring%20for%20their%20aging%20parents%20and%20dependent%20children%2C%20has%20fallen%20behind%20in%20their%20financial%20savings.%20A%20study%20conducted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.nationwide.com%2Fmore-than-half-of-gen-x-investors-support-parents-or-children-forcing-early-retirement-withdrawals--debt%2F%3Futm_source%3DNWNewsroom%26utm_medium%3DNewsroom%26utm_campaign%3DNWNewsroom%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%20Nationwide%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%2056%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20were%20financially%20supporting%20either%20their%20parents%20or%20their%20kids.%20About%20a%20fifth%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20taking%20care%20of%20a%20parent%20said%20they%20had%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-charts-show-struggles-bills-spending-need-more-work-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edebt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20similar%20portion%20said%20they%20were%20unable%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconnect.guardiangroupbenefits.com%2Fl%2F503851%2F2023-12-15%2F6yw1b6%2F503851%2F1702675399bBkGiG78%2FGuardian_12th_Annual_WBS_Standing_Up_and_Stepping_In_1215.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20adults%20who%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20spouse%2C%20older%20parent%20or%20relative%2C%20or%20child%20with%20special%20needs%20has%20grown%20from%2043.5%20million%20in%202015%20to%2053%20million%20in%202021%2C%20per%20a%20report%20from%20the%20insurance%20provider%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20survey%20of%2035-%20to%2060-year-olds%20conducted%20by%20Carewell%20found%20that%2075%25%20of%20those%20taking%20care%20of%20both%20a%20parent%20and%20a%20child%20said%20they%20struggled%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esave%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%2063%25%20said%20they%20lived%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%20Meanwhile%2C%20adult%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.aarp.org%2F2024-5-16-US-Workforce-Report-70-Caregivers-Difficulty-Balancing-Career-Caregiving-Responsibilities%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaregivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20provided%20around%20%24600%20billion%20worth%20of%20unpaid%20labor%20last%20year%2C%20noted%20a%20separate%20report%20from%20the%20AARP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Goldstein%2C%20a%20financial%20planner%20at%20Prudential%2C%20said%20he%20frequently%20works%20with%20clients%20struggling%20to%20care%20for%20their%20parents%20as%20they%20get%20older.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20his%20clients%20are%20experiencing%20financial%20stress%20as%20a%20result%20of%20caretaking%20and%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20saving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20may%20need%20to%20bank%20on%20their%20own%20children%20taking%20care%20of%20them%20in%20the%20future%2C%20he%20suggested%2C%20given%20how%20much%20they've%20sacrificed%20in%20their%20own%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20to%20reduce%20what%20you%20put%20towards%20retirement%20is%20going%20to%20put%20you%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20you%20might%20not%20have%20assets%20now%2C%20and%20you%20could%20%E2%80%94%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20call%20it%20a%20burden%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20might%20become%20this%20responsibility%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20assets%20to%20cover%20a%20facility%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20may%20need%20to%20consider%20working%20for%20longer%20than%20they%20originally%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20through%20ballooning%20Medicaid%20costs%2C%20taxpayers%20may%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20the%20growing%20long-term%20care%20crisis.%20An%20increasing%20number%20of%20older%20people%20don't%20have%20kids%20or%20spouses%20to%20take%20care%20of%20them%20as%20they%20age%2C%20and%20those%20that%20end%20up%20needing%20long-term%20care%20may%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20Medicaid.%20About%20a%20fifth%20of%20baby%20boomer%20women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fsarazeffgeber%2F2019%2F01%2F28%2Fchild-free-in-america-a-large-piece-of-the-solo-aging-pie%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DI%2520bet%2520you%2520do%252C%2520because%2Chelp%2520them%2520as%2520they%2520age.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20have%20any%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20those%20who%20do%20have%20kids%20have%20fewer%2C%20on%20average%2C%20than%20previous%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e5498074-f0a9-4423-aa0a-ece7367d599e%5C%22%3EA%20government-aided%20solution%20for%20long-term%20care%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20argues%20that%20the%20private%20long-term%20insurance%20market%20is%20suffering%20from%20%26quot%3Ba%20clear%20market%20failure%26quot%3B%20and%20policymakers%20need%20to%20step%20in%20to%20create%20a%20public%20option%20for%20middle-income%20people%20and%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcCracken%20said%20that%20in%20order%20to%20scale%20some%20of%20the%20most%20effective%20models%20of%20assisted%20living%20and%20other%20long-term%20care%2C%20private%20providers%20will%20need%20more%20government%20incentives%20and%20partnerships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20argued%20that%20public%20long-term%20care%20insurance%20would%20work%20well%20if%20most%20people%20paid%20into%20it%20because%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fnews%2Fpress%2F2017%2F08%2F28%2Findex1.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOnly%2520about%2520one%252Dthird%2520of%2520Americans%2520between%2520the%2Ccompletely%2520covered%2520by%2520private%2520or%2520public%2520insurance.%26amp%3Btext%3D%25E2%2580%259CLong%252Dterm%2520care%2520insurance%2520is%2520only%2520taken%2520up%2Cindividuals%2520in%2520their%2520early%252060s%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520Hurd%2520said.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelatively%20small%20number%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20older%20people%20require%20the%20most%20expensive%20care%2C%20like%2024%2F7%20nursing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20option%20could%20resemble%20an%20earned%20benefit%2C%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%2C%20funded%20by%20a%20mandatory%20tax%20that%20people%20pay%20throughout%20their%20lives%20and%20collect%20when%20they%20retire.%20Rep.%20Tom%20Suozzi%2C%20a%20New%20York%20Democrat%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F12%2F05%2Fmany-people-cant-afford-long-term-care-how-a-federal-program-may-help.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20create%20a%20public%20insurance%20program%20for%20catastrophic%20long-term%20care%20funded%20by%20a%20payroll%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20have%20begun%20to%20address%20the%20issue.%20Washington%20State%20recently%20passed%20a%200.6%25%20payroll%20tax%20to%20fund%20a%20new%20universal%20long-term%20care%20insurance%20program%20called%20WA%20Cares%2C%20which%20provides%20%2436%2C500%20in%20care%20per%20person%2C%20and%20will%20increase%20with%20inflation%20in%20future%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGilles%20said%20she%20wants%20to%20see%20the%20government%20or%20care%20providers%20figure%20out%20a%20way%20to%20lower%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20got%20to%20provide%20more%20support%20to%20families%20going%20through%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20got%20to%20either%20make%20it%20more%20affordable%2C%20or%20they%20need%20to%20provide%20more%20resources%2C%20or%20not%20make%20it%20so%20expensive%20so%20that%20it's%20attainable%20for%20anybody%20at%20any%20income%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20or%20someone%20you%20care%20for%20struggling%20with%20long-term%20care%20costs%3F%20Email%20this%20reporter%20to%20share%20your%20story%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aerelman%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eerelman%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-xers-burdened-long-term-care-costs-for-boomers-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736591701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678041fd8951662c9f1f832f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-xers-burdened-long-term-care-costs-for-boomers-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rising%20long-term%20healthcare%20costs%20mean%20many%20baby%20boomers%20are%20unequipped%20to%20support%20themsel